            "title": "Making Sounds",
            "created_at": "Thu, 09/02/2021 - 16:44",
            "updated_at": "Thu, 09/02/2021 - 17:00",
            "summary": "Materials You Need: Picture cards; or just telling stories and making sounds. ",
            "body": "<p class=\"paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Materials You Need</span></b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">: </span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Picture cards; or just telling stories and making sounds. </span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">What You Can Do Together</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">: With this activity, you will help your little one to identify images and make short sounds.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Before starting, remember to prepare the space for your little one. Place him/her in a comfortable space, in a chair or on some pillows in front of you.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Gather your cards with images, drawings, or photographs, show them to your little one by one, and mention the name of the image on the card. Wait for your child to recognize the object and motivate them to make and repeat the sound the image on the card makes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Use pictures of object that are familiar to them, and describe the objects using short words like \"mama\", \"papa\".</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">What Your Child is Learning</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">: With this activity, you will be helping your little one to identify images and make short sounds like \"ma\", \"pa\", \"ta\".</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n",
