            "body": "<p class=\"paragraph\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Materials You Need</span></b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">: Small toys for your little one, for example, rattles, blocks, rings, dolls; Soft blanket; Pillow</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">What You Can Do Together</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">: Before starting the activity with your little one, prepare the environment. Place the blankets that you are going to use on a carpet or flat surface. Then place the pillow on the blankets. Your little one must be put down with her/his chest on the pillow for the activity to be effective.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">Next, place the toys some distance away so that he/she should reach out and pick up the toy.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">The objective of this activity is for your baby to begin to utilize and exercise muscles in her/his body and to stimulate hand-eye coordination.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">What Your Child is Learning</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif\">: This activity helps your child develop fine motor skills and control of their smaller muscles.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n",
